# Worktree Isolation

- Do not implement code changes directly in the host checkout when it may contain unrelated edits or concurrent agent work.
- Start each implementation task in an isolated git worktree on a dedicated branch based on `main`.
- Prefer Cursor isolated runners/worktree-backed execution when available before touching repository files.
- Keep host checkout read-only for exploration, review, and context gathering.
- Only include task-related files in commits and pull requests from the isolated branch.

## Required Workflow

1. **Check open PRs first**: Run `gh pr list --state open` to identify parallel work that may conflict. Avoid branches that touch the same files.
2. **Create worktree**: `git worktree add .worktrees/<task-name> -b <branch-name> main` from the host checkout. Always branch from `main`.
3. **Implement** inside that isolated worktree only. Never edit host checkout files.
4. **Validate locally** before committing (run from the worktree root). The root `Makefile` is the single source of truth for all quality gates:
   - `make test` (unit tests — backend + frontend)
   - `make test-integration` (integration tests)
   - `make validate` (all linters + type checking)
   - `make pre-commit` (pre-commit hooks on all files)
5. **Commit** with a descriptive message following the repo's conventional-commit style.
6. **Push and open a PR**: `git push -u origin HEAD` then `gh pr create`. Never leave uncommitted work without a PR.
7. **Monitor CI**: Run `gh pr checks <PR-NUMBER>` and poll until all checks complete. If any check fails:
   - Read the failure logs: `gh run view <RUN-ID> --job <JOB-ID> --log-failed`
   - Fix in the worktree, commit, and push again.
   - Re-monitor until green (or confirm failure is unrelated, e.g. billing/infra).
8. **Report** the PR URL and CI status to the user before finishing.

## Checklist (agent must complete ALL before finishing a task)

- [ ] Checked `gh pr list --state open` for conflicts
- [ ] Worktree created from `main` (verify with `git merge-base --is-ancestor main HEAD`)
- [ ] All changes are inside the worktree, not the host checkout
- [ ] `make validate` passes (lint + typecheck)
- [ ] `make test` passes (unit tests)
- [ ] `make test-integration` passes (integration tests)
- [ ] Any **new or modified Makefile targets** have been executed at least once and produce the expected result
- [ ] Changes committed with a descriptive message
- [ ] Branch pushed to remote
- [ ] PR created with summary and test plan
- [ ] CI checks monitored and status reported to user
